Title: Extends provisions of law relating to the use of electronic means for the commencement and filing of papers in certain actions or proceedings
Summary: Extends provisions of law relating to the use of electronic means for the commencement and filing of papers in certain actions or proceedings until September 1, 2021.
ActClause: AN ACT to amend chapter 237 of the laws of 2015 amending the judiciary law, the civil practice law and rules and other laws relating to use of electronic means for the commencement and filing of papers in certain actions and proceedings, in relation to the effectiveness thereof
